us%20that%20we%20went%20to%20ski%20races%20to%20see%20500%20of%20our%20closest%20friends%2C%26quot%3B%20Nelson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20as%20snowless%20winters%20become%20more%20common%20across%20the%20country%2C%20these%20traditions%20are%20going%20to%20be%20harder%20and%20harder%20to%20maintain.%20As%20we%20lose%20the%20snow%2C%20we're%20also%20losing%20part%20of%20our%20identities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20was%20growing%20up%20in%20Minnesota%2C%20winter%20was%20omnipresent.%20Every%20December%2C%20the%20Minneapolis%20lakes%20would%20freeze%20over%2C%20creating%20entirely%20new%20public%20parks.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F122-fishermen-stranded-on-an-ice-floe-minnesota-lake-rescued-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIce%20fishers%3C%2Fa%3E%20would%20drill%20holes%20and%20set%20up%20semipermanent%20houses%20on%20the%20ice%2C%20skijorers%20would%20train%20their%20dogs%20to%20pull%20them%20along%20the%20frozen%20lakes%20as%20they%20skied%20behind%2C%20rinks%20would%20be%20cleared%20and%20maintained%20for%20pond%20hockey%20and%20ice%20skating%2C%20intrepid%20swimmers%20did%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcold-plunging-every-day-has-really-helped-my-anxiety-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecold%20plunges%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20holes%20carved%20into%20the%20lake%2C%20and%20artists%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fartshantyprojects.org%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecapitalized%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20lack%20of%20building%20codes%20to%20set%20up%20shanties%20and%20interactive%20sculptures%20on%20the%20seasonal%20public%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20many%20ways%2C%20snow%2C%20ice%2C%20and%20freezing%20temperatures%20are%20baked%20into%20the%20cultural%20DNA%20of%20Minneapolis%20and%20communities%20across%20the%20country.%20But%20this%20year%2C%20the%20casualties%20of%20a%20snowless%20winter%20%E2%80%94%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.startribune.com%2Fthese-minnesota-winter-festivals-were-altered-postponed-or-canceled-by-warm-weather%2F600339459%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecanceled%20ski%20races%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20ice-fishing%20contests%20to%20nonexistent%20ice%20palaces%20%E2%80%94%20are%20stacking%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20weeks%2C%20it%20wasn't%20clear%20whether%20the%20Cross-Country%20World%20Cup%2C%20an%20international%20ski%20race%20that%20took%20place%20in%20Minneapolis%20on%20Presidents%20Day%20weekend%2C%20would%20happen.%20It%20was%20the%20first%20time%20in%20two%20decades%20that%20it%20was%20hosted%20in%20the%20US.%20But%20the%20warm%20temperatures%20and%20lack%20of%20snow%20leading%20up%20to%20the%20weekend%20left%20organizers%20rattled%20%E2%80%94%20a%20possibility%20that%20Claire%20Wilson%2C%20the%20executive%20director%20of%20the%20organization%20that%20hosted%20the%20event%2C%20the%20Loppet%20Foundation%2C%20couldn't%20have%20imagined%20when%20planning%20started%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20course%20for%20the%20Cross%20Country%20World%20Cup%20has%20just%20enough%20snow.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65cf6740a610a9069d59bb36%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThis%20year's%20course%20is%20a%20lone%20ribbon%20of%20snow%20amid%20a%20sea%20of%20brown%20grass%20and%20trees.%3Cp%3EThe%20Loppet%20Foundation%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20said%2C%20'We'll%20do%20it%20in%20February%20because%20there's%20no%20way%20we%20won't%20have%20snow%20in%20February%2C'%26quot%3B%20Wilson%20recalled%20last%20month.%20%26quot%3BI%20could%20not%20have%20envisioned%20a%20scenario%20where%20we%20could%20not%20make%20snow%20or%20we%20had%20no%20snow%20in%20January.%20It's%20January%2C%20and%20we%20can't.%20It's%2050%20degrees%20outside.%26quot%3B%20The%20race%20is%20still%20set%20to%20take%20place%2C%20thanks%20to%20a%20late-January%20cold%20snap%20that%20allowed%20the%20organizers%20to%20make%20enough%20snow%20to%20cover%20the%20course.%20%26quot%3BIt%20will%20not%20be%20the%20winter%20wonderland%20we%20had%20hoped%20for%2C%26quot%3B%20Wilson%20wrote%20in%20an%20email%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20it%20will%20be%20something!%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Loppet%20Foundation%20also%20works%20with%20schools%20in%20north%20Minneapolis%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-many-calories-does-cross-country-skiing-burn-2018-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eteach%20kids%20how%20to%20ski%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20this%20year%2C%20Wilson's%20team%20has%20been%20stuck%20inside.%20%26quot%3BThere%20was%20a%20whole%20lot%20of%20teaching%20kids%20how%20to%20put%20on%20their%20skis%20in%20the%20gym%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Americans%20used%20to%20consistently%20frigid%2C%20snowy%20winters%2C%20this%20year's%20tepid%20and%20rainy%20weather%20hangs%20uncomfortably.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20joy%20that%20comes%20from%20being%20in%20that%20change%20of%20seasons%2C%26quot%3B%20Wilson%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20just%20think%20we're%20missing%20that%20joy.%20I%20hear%20it%20from%20my%20staff%2C%20I%20hear%20it%20from%20our%20participants.%20There's%20a%20lot%20of%20folks%20who%20are%20just%20really%20missing%20winter%2C%20and%20it's%20showing%20up%20as%20grief.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeter%20McClelland%2C%20a%2055-year-old%20Minnesotan%2C%20is%20also%20feeling%20the%20loss%20from%20this%20year's%20weird%20winter.%20On%20a%20winter%20camping%20trip%20in%20college%2C%20McClelland%20fell%20in%20love%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-its-like-to-go-dog-sledding-2013-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edog%20sledding%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20before%20long%2C%20he%20got%20a%20gig%20guiding%20dog-sled%20trips.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20supposed%20to%20guide%20for%20only%20a%20year%20or%20two%20before%20I%20went%20to%20grad%20school%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20with%20a%20laugh.%20%26quot%3BI%20haven't%20been%20to%20grad%20school%20yet.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20McClelland%2C%20dog%20sledding%20is%20an%20almost%20spiritual%20experience.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20you're%20working%20with%20an%20animal%20together%20to%20accomplish%20a%20common%20goal%2C%20it's%20a%20deeper%20connection%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcClelland%20started%20his%20own%20guiding%20business%20in%20Minnesota%20in%201995%20and%20now%20has%20a%20team%20of%20100%20dogs%20that%20he%20leads%20to%20bring%20visitors%20on%20tours%20through%20the%20woods.%20The%20week%20between%20Christmas%20and%20New%20Year's%20is%20usually%20his%20busiest%20season.%20This%20year%2C%20however%2C%20it%20rained%20over%20Christmas%2C%20and%20there%20was%20no%20snow%20%E2%80%94%20a%20first%20for%20McClelland%2C%20and%20a%20real%20hit%20to%20his%20business.%20%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20know%20how%20the%20rest%20of%20winter%20is%20going%20to%20go.%20But%20we're%20going%20to%20lose%20a%20minimum%20of%20a%20third%20of%20our%20businesses%2C%20and%20I%20do%20not%20expect%20to%20be%20solvent%20again%20until%20March%20of%202025%2C%20if%20everything%20goes%20right%2C%26quot%3B%20McClelland%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222496%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Sled%20dogs%20leading%20a%20sled%20through%20the%20snow%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65cf6793a610a9069d59bb72%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221664%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFor%20McClelland%2C%20dog%20sledding%20is%20an%20almost%20spiritual%20experience.%20%3Cp%3EPeter%20McClelland%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20warmer%20weather%20eating%20into%20the%20peak%20of%20the%20season%2C%20it's%20getting%20harder%20and%20harder%20to%20sustain%20a%20winter-based%20business.%20%26quot%3BI%20do%20not%20feel%20that%20I%20have%20a%20business%20I%20could%20turn%20over%20to%20my%20kids%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20impact%20on%20his%20company%20isn't%20the%20only%20thing%20McClelland%20is%20mourning.%20%26quot%3BThe%20history%20of%20sled%20dogs%20and%20humans%20is%20so%20deep%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BTo%20travel%20together%20is%20just%20such%20a%20rich%20experience%20and%20part%20of%20human%20history%20that%2C%20if%20we%20lose%20it%2C%20we've%20really%20lost%20something.%20And%20people%20won't%20even%20know%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20much%20of%20the%20country%2C%20long%2C%20harsh%20winters%20aren't%20exactly%20celebrated.%20Even%20in%20Minnesota%2C%20the%20only%20thing%20locals%20love%20more%20than%20winter%20is%20threatening%20to%20move%20to%20warmer%20states.%20As%20a%20kid%2C%20I%20remember%20frantically%20trying%20to%20melt%20the%20icicles%20in%20my%20ponytail%20with%20my%20palms%20so%20my%20hair%20wouldn't%20snap%20off%20after%20walking%20to%20school%20in%20subzero%20temperatures.%20On%20those%20days%2C%20I'm%20sure%20I%20fantasized%20about%20warmer%2C%20sunnier%20weather%20too.%20But%20now%2C%20after%20two%20nearly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fextreme-weather-events-nyc-whiplash-big-blizzard-snow-storm-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esnow-free%20years%20in%20New%20York%20City%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20the%20climate%20was%20recently%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thecut.com%2F2020%2F07%2Fnew-york-citys-climate-reclassified-as-humid-subtropical.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereclassified%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20%26quot%3Bhumid%20subtropical%2C%26quot%3B%20I%20miss%20those%20frigid%20January%20mornings%20filled%20with%20frozen%20tree%20branches%20that%20look%20dipped%20in%20glass.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20places%20with%20deep%20winter%20traditions%2C%20the%20changing%20climate%20could%20mean%20a%20permanent%20reconfiguration%20of%20our%20relationship%20with%20the%20season.%20In%202005%2C%20the%20Australian%20environmental%20philosopher%20Glenn%20Albrecht%20coined%20the%20term%20%26quot%3Bsolastalgia%26quot%3B%20to%20mean%20a%20kind%20of%20homesickness%20%E2%80%94%20not%20for%20another%20place%20or%20time%20but%20for%20a%20climate%20or%20environment%20that%20no%20longer%20exists.%20To%20me%2C%20the%20feeling%20combines%20grief%20with%20a%20sense%20of%20uneasiness%2C%20a%20vague%20perception%20that%20things%20aren't%20as%20they%20should%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20reason%20that%20solastalgia%20is%20so%20powerful%20isn't%20just%20that%20we're%20mourning%20a%20specific%20environment%20or%20season%20but%20also%20that%20the%20changing%20environment%20alters%20our%20shared%20sense%20of%20identity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20actually%20think%20we're%20grieving%20a%20changing%20environment%20very%20little%2C%26quot%3B%20Alexander%20Lee%2C%20an%20environmental%20philosopher%20at%20Alaska%20Pacific%20University%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20way%20that%20the%20change%20takes%20on%20any%20sort%20of%20either%20moral%20weight%20or%20cultural%20weight%2C%20or%20emotional%20weight%2C%20the%20way%20it%20takes%20on%20value%2C%20is%20how%20I%20relate%20to%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20it's%20not%20just%20the%20changing%20winters%20that%20we're%20grieving%20but%20also%20the%20parts%20of%20ourselves%20that%20are%20changing%20with%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20event%20that%20survived%20this%20year's%20%26quot%3Blost%20winter%26quot%3B%20was%20the%20Great%20Northern%2C%20a%2010-day%20festival%20in%20Minneapolis%20dedicated%20to%20the%20majesty%20of%20winter.%20Today%20it's%20almost%20as%20much%20about%20the%20loss%20of%20winter%20as%20it%20is%20about%20the%20season%20itself.%20%26quot%3BThe%20festival%20demonstrates%20how%20deeply%20winter%20has%20shaped%20our%20culture%20%E2%80%94%20what%20it%20does%20to%20us%2C%20how%20it%20makes%20us%20who%20we%20are%2C%26quot%3B%20Kate%20Nordstrum%2C%20the%20chief%20programming%20officer%20for%20the%20Great%20Northern%2C%20said.%20In%20recent%20years%2C%20there%20has%20been%20an%20increasing%20emphasis%20on%20the%20climate%20crisis%3B%20this%20year%2C%20along%20with%20events%20such%20as%20a%20sauna%20village%20and%20ice%20bar%2C%20there%20were%20talks%20on%20climate%20policy%20and%20climate-career%20options.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20meant%20to%20be%20a%20celebration%20of%20winter%2C%26quot%3B%20Nordstrum%20said.%20Now%20it's%20also%20about%20the%20%26quot%3Bfight%20to%20preserve%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20who%20have%20grown%20up%20in%20the%20North%2C%20whether%20it's%20here%20or%20somewhere%20else%20that%20has%20deep%20winter%20snow%2C%20are%20starting%20to%20think%20back%20to%20childhood%2C%20and%20it%20almost%20feels%20like%20a%20dream%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20wonder%3A%20We%20may%20have%20some%20more%20glimpses%20of%20winter%20coming%20still%2C%20but%20will%20it%20continue%20fading%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222312%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jocie%20Nelson%20skiing%20the%20Birkie%20with%20her%20infant%20son%20on%20her%20back.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65cf6a626fcb546d2d509280%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20who%20have%20grown%20up%20in%20the%20North%20are%20starting%20to%20think%20back%20to%20childhood%20and%20it%20almost%20feels%20like%20a%20dream.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EThe%20American%20Birkebeiner%20Ski%20Foundation%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20question%20weighs%20on%20me%20more%20heavily%20with%20each%20passing%20year.%20For%20me%2C%20winter%20has%20always%20been%20about%20the%20collective%20identity%20that%20we%20shape%20in%20these%20shared%20traditions%20in%20the%20cold%20%E2%80%94%20the%20intangible%20joy%20McClelland%20finds%20in%20his%20bond%20with%20his%20dogs%2C%20the%20community%20Nelson%20has%20built%20over%20decades%20at%20the%20Birkie%2C%20and%20the%20memories%20I%20share%20with%20childhood%20friends%2C%20sledding%20on%20the%20streets%20in%20a%20snowstorm%2C%20giggling%20and%20shrieking%20as%20we%20jumped%20into%20a%20frozen%20lake%20in%20January.%20These%20moments%20made%20up%20the%20old%20sense%20of%20normal%20that%20is%20being%20slowly%20eroded%20by%20the%20climate%20crisis.%20What%20can%20I%20someday%20share%20with%20my%20kids%20about%20a%20season%20that%20will%20be%2C%20in%20a%20few%20decades%2C%20so%20different%20from%20what%20I%20remember%20from%20my%20childhood%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConnelly%20of%20the%20Birkebeiner%20Ski%20Foundation%20is%20optimistic%20that%20winter%20culture%20will%20live%20on.%20He%20recalled%20the%201981%20Birkie%20when%20it%20was%2063%20degrees%20and%20hundreds%20of%20volunteers%20showed%20up%20to%20shovel%20snow%20onto%20the%20course%20to%20make%20the%20race%20possible.%20%26quot%3BThat%20just%20speaks%20to%20that%20resiliency%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20make%20lemonade.%20If%20we%20get%20low%20snow%2C%20we're%20going%20to%20find%20that%20snow%20and%20use%20it%20as%20best%20we%20can%20to%20get%20out%20there.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWilson%20of%20the%20Loppet%20Foundation%20is%20less%20certain.%20Without%20snow%20and%20freezing%20temperatures%2C%20she%20said%2C%20winter%20is%20going%20to%20be%20different.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20going%20to%20shift%20our%20identity%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20think%20I%20have%20the%20answer%20to%20what%20that%20is%20going%20to%20look%20like.%20But%20the%20shift%20is%20underway.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Falexandria-herr%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EAlexandria%20Herr%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20climate%20and%20environment%20writer%20from%20Minnesota%20residing%20in%20Brooklyn.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdeath-of-snow-america-midwest-warm-winter-skiing-climate-change-2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%