20the%20Russian%20warship%20Caesar%20Kunikov%20with%20a%20sea%20drone%20last%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20the%20latest%20in%20a%20series%20of%20victories%20for%20Ukraine%2C%20which%20has%20a%20tiny%20navy%2C%20against%20Russia's%20much%20bigger%20Black%20Sea%20fleet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20seems%20that%20it%20had%20become%20impossible%20to%20ignore%20the%20latest%20heavy%20losses%20of%20the%20fleet%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20War%20Informant%20channel%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUK%20military%20intelligence%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FDefenceHQ%2Fstatus%2F1759145815946195025%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eon%20Sunday%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20that%20Sokolov's%20dismissal%20was%20%26quot%3Bhighly%20likely%20to%20be%20a%20result%20of%20Ukraine's%20success%20in%20sinking%20various%20ships%20under%20his%20command.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine%20said%20it%20had%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-thrashing-russia-black-sea-fleet-no-navy-sevastopol-2024-2%3Fr%3DUS%26IR%3DT%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20destroyed%20around%2030%25%20of%20Russia's%20fleet%2C%20%3C%2Fa%3Eenabling%20it%20to%20prevent%20Russia%20from%20blockading%20Ukrainian%20ships%20transporting%20grain%20and%20limiting%20the%20ability%20of%20warships%20to%20strike%20targets%20in%20Ukraine.%20The%20grain%20trade%20is%20a%20crucial%20part%20of%20Ukraine's%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnalysts%20claim%20that%20Ukraine's%20use%20of%20drones%20and%20long-range%20missiles%20has%20been%20vital%20for%20overturning%20Russia's%20advantages%20at%20sea.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20first%2C%20Russia%20may%20have%20appeared%20to%20hold%20almost%20all%20the%20naval%20cards%20in%20the%20Black%20Sea%2C%20but%20Ukraine's%20strategic%20approach%20at%20sea%20and%20innovative%20use%20of%20emerging%20technology%20has%20led%20to%20several%20successes%2C%26quot%3B%20Nicholas%20Johnson%2C%20an%20analyst%20at%20the%20RAND%20Corporation%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUkrainian%20success%20in%20this%20sea%20denial%20approach%20has%20largely%20been%20due%20to%20their%20innovative%20and%20skillful%20use%20of%20emerging%20technologies.%C2%A0%20The%20combination%20of%20uncrewed%20surface%20vessels%20and%20long-range%20missiles%20have%20provided%20Ukraine's%20nearly%20non-existent%20navy%20with%20an%20asymmetric%20capability%20to%20hold%20Russian%20controlled%20ports%20and%20Black%20Sea%20Fleet%20at%20risk.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine's%20attacks%20have%20included%20strikes%20on%20Sevastopol%2C%20the%20base%20of%20Russia's%20Black%20Sea%20fleet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20June%20strike%20on%20Sevastopol%20forced%20Russia%20to%20cancel%20its%20Navy%20Day%20celebrations%2C%20while%20a%20missile%20attack%20on%20September%2013%20damaged%20a%20Russian%20submarine%20and%20warship.%20Another%20missile%20attack%20on%20September%2023%20targeted%20Russia's%20naval%20command%20center%2C%20and%20Ukraine%20initially%20claimed%20that%20Sokolov%20was%20among%20the%2034%20officers%20it%20had%20killed%20in%20that%20attack.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Sokolov%20later%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-admiral-sokolov-not-dead-video-suggests-despite-ukraine-claim-2023-9%3Fr%3DUS%26IR%3DT%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eappeared%20in%20a%20Kremlin%20video%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20a%20conference%20of%20military%20leaders%2C%20apparently%20showing%20he%20survived.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWar%20bloggers%20blamed%20Sokolov%20for%20a%20series%20of%20mistakes%20that%20they%20said%20had%20been%20among%20the%20reasons%20for%20Russia's%20defeats%20in%20the%20Back%20Sea%2C%20reported%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.themoscowtimes.com%2F2024%2F02%2F15%2Fblack-sea-fleet-commander-sacked-over-warships-sinking-russian-pro-war-bloggers-say-a84091%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Moscow%20Times.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESergei%20Markov%2C%20a%20former%20Kremlin%20advisor%2C%20also%20claimed%20Sokolov%20had%20been%20removed%2C%20without%20citing%20sources%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Frussian-bloggers-say-fleet-commander-fired-after-latest-ukrainian-ship-attack-2024-02-15%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%20Reuters.%20%3C%2Fa%3EThere%20was%20no%20official%20confirmation%20of%20his%20dismissal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESokolov%20had%20taken%20over%20as%20commander%20of%20the%20fleet%20in%20September%202022%2C%20replacing%20Admiral%20Igor%20Osipov%2C%20only%20months%20after%20Ukraine%20sank%20Russia's%20Black%20Sea%20flagship%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20Moskva.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%20rarely%20publicly%20confirms%20the%20replacement%20of%20senior%20commanders%2C%20and%20Russia's%20defense%20ministry%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fputin-fired-admiral-black-sea-fleet-ukraine-defeats-navy-sokolov-2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708336692000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65cf3c256fcb546d2d508381%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fputin-fired-admiral-black-sea-fleet-ukraine-defeats-navy-sokolov-2024-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Ukraine%20claims%20to%20have%20destroyed%2030%25%20of%20Russia's%20Black%20Sea%20Fleet%20during%20Admiral%20Viktor%20Sokolov's%20time%20in%20charge.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22tporter%40businessinsider.com%20(Tom%20Porter)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fputin-fired-admiral-black-sea-fleet-ukraine-defeats-navy-sokolov-2024-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Shilpa-Raj%20to%20perform%20at%20Rakul's%20wedding%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708336631000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F