em%3E%2C%20released%20last%20month%20across%20the%20US%2C%20Dr%20B.R.%20Ambedkar%20has%20made%20an%20entry%20on%20the%20big%20screen%20in%20Hollywood.%20The%20film%20directed%20by%20Ava%20DuVernay%C2%A0is%20based%20on%20Isabel%20Wilson%E2%80%99s%20book%20%3Cem%3ECaste%3A%20The%20Origins%20of%20Our%20Discontents%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Ambedkar%E2%80%99s%20writings%20have%20spread%20across%20the%20world%2C%20there%20is%20a%20new-found%20interest%20in%20his%20persona%20and%20his%20work.%20A%20Hollywood%20movie%20showing%20an%20%E2%80%9Cuntouchable%E2%80%9D%20boy%20Bhima%20sitting%20outside%20a%20classroom%20and%20later%20as%20a%20young%20man%20walking%20around%20Columbia%20University%20reading%20books%20is%20indeed%20very%20compelling.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FpAweg5PaMuw%3Fsi%3DIxa58tIMJ5z-7ZqL%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThrough%20this%20two-and-a-half-hour%20movie%2C%20DuVernay%2C%20known%20for%20her%20Oscar%20nominated%20%3Cem%3ESelma%20(2014)%3C%2Fem%3E%20tries%20to%20establish%20a%20compelling%20and%20convincing%20link%20between%20caste%20discrimination%20in%20India%2C%20racial%20apartheid%20in%20America%20and%20the%20persecution%20of%20Jews%20in%20Germany.%20%3Cem%3EOrigin%3C%2Fem%3E%20essentially%20brings%20on%20screen%2C%20the%20journey%20of%20the%20author%20Isabel%20Wilkerson%20(played%20by%20Aunjanue%20Ellis-Taylor).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20film%20tries%20to%20underscore%20that%20it%20is%20not%20race%20but%20caste%20which%20is%20the%20overarching%20binding%20force%20%E2%80%94%20a%20skeleton%20%E2%80%94%20to%20various%20other%20forms%20of%20discrimination.%20The%20movie%20covers%20the%20history%20of%20three%20countries%20%E2%80%94%20Germany%2C%20America%20and%20India%20%E2%80%94%20to%20find%20a%20common%20thread%20among%20discrimination%20across%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGaurav%20Pathania%2C%20assistant%20professor%20of%20Sociology%20at%20Easter%20Mennonite%20University%2C%20Virginia%20plays%20the%20role%20of%20Ambedkar%20in%20the%20film.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20trigger%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20one%20of%20the%20scenes%2C%20Wilkerson%20is%20shown%20opening%20Dr%20Ambedkar%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Annihilation%20of%20Caste%3C%2Fem%3E%20as%20she%20tries%20to%20find%20answers%20to%20a%20range%20of%20questions%20that%20hit%20her%20after%20she%20comes%20to%20know%20of%20the%20death%20of%20an%20innocent%20young%20black%20man%2C%20called%20Treyvon%20Martin%2C%20killed%20in%202012%20for%20merely%20walking%20in%20the%20neighbourhood%20because%20he%20was%20considered%20a%20%E2%80%98threat%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20shatters%20Wilkerson%20to%20the%20core.%20She%20instantly%20drops%20her%20current%20project%20and%20decides%20to%20understand%20the%20root%20cause%20of%20racism%20and%20its%20nuances%20in%20the%20US.%20In%20her%20quest%2C%20she%20travelled%20to%20Germany%20and%20India%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20questions%20arise%20in%20her%20mind%20like%20Jews%20and%20Aryans%20are%20both%20white%20then%20how%20did%20the%20Nazis%20separate%20one%20from%20the%20other%3B%20all%20Indians%20are%20mostly%20brown%20then%20how%20did%20they%20separate%20the%20%E2%80%98touchable%E2%80%99%20from%20the%20%E2%80%98untouchables%E2%80%99.%20She%20was%20intrigued%20if%20there%20was%20a%20common%20thread%20of%20prevention%20of%20interracial%20or%20inter-caste%20marriages%2C%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20preserve%20the%20%E2%80%98purity%E2%80%99%20of%20race%20or%20caste.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20300px)%2085vw%2C%20300px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F19150407%2FScreen-Shot-2024-02-19-at-3.03.38-PM-300x134.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22300%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F19150407%2FScreen-Shot-2024-02-19-at-3.03.38-PM-300x134.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F19150407%2FScreen-Shot-2024-02-19-at-3.03.38-PM.png%20824w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-697793%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22134%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20still%20from%20the%20film%20%E2%80%98Origin%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInitially%2C%20any%20suggestion%20of%20a%20connection%20of%20caste%20is%20rejected%20by%20many%20of%20her%20colleagues%20and%20family%20members.%20But%2C%20what%20follows%20are%20answers%20to%20these%20questions.%20Along%20with%20her%2C%20the%20audience%20is%20then%20taken%20to%20an%20insightful%20and%20interesting%20journey%20across%20the%20world%20that%20provides%20new%20discoveries%2C%20theories%20and%20evidences%20to%20prove%20the%20linkage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWilkerson%C2%A0gives%20specific%20examples%20while%20proving%20her%20point%20%E2%80%94%20how%20%E2%80%9Ccaste%E2%80%9D%20is%20an%20inherent%20thing%20such%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cbone%E2%80%9D%20whereas%20race%20acts%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cskin%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20movie%20reveals%20how%20Nazis%20were%20inspired%20by%20a%20segregation%20and%20disenfranchisement%20system%20of%20the%201890s%20known%20as%20the%20Jim%20Crow%20Law%20in%20the%20US%20where%20African%20Americans%20were%20separated%20from%20commonplaces%20such%20as%20schools%2C%20toilets%2C%20buses%20and%20trains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20movie%20shows%20how%20the%20strict%20maintenance%20of%20endogamy%20comes%20to%20play%20at%20any%20cost%20in%20all%20three%20forms%20of%20discrimination%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Holocaust%2C%20in%20the%20Jim%20Crow%20era%20and%20in%20India%20%E2%80%94%20such%20examples%2C%20the%20narration%20and%20the%20powerful%20scenery%20makes%20her%20hypothesis%20convincing.%20Some%20members%20of%20the%20audience%20were%20also%20seen%20clapping%20at%20the%20powerful%20ending%20of%20the%20film.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20it%20concentrates%20on%20the%20past%20and%20the%20present%20life%20of%20Wilkerson%2C%20it%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20sound%20like%20a%20documentary%20nor%20a%20biography%20of%20the%20author.%20The%20director%20keeps%20the%20audience%E2%80%99s%20attention%20glued.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Ambedkar%20angle%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20film%2C%20Wilkerson%20meets%20Indian%20scholar%20Dr%20Suraj%20Yengde%20from%20Harvard%20during%20her%20visit%20to%20the%20country.%20He%20gives%20her%20additional%20insights%20on%20the%20caste%20system.%20Yengde%20asserts%20that%20Ambedkar%20is%20close%20to%20the%20African%20Americans.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EOrigin%3C%2Fi%3E%20underlines%20how%20caste%20is%20an%20intrinsic%20factor%20in%20a%20developing%20country%20like%20India%20where%20there%20still%20continues%20an%20inhuman%20practice%20of%20manual%20scavenging%3A%20Dalits%20enter%20into%20a%20manhole%20full%20of%20human%20excreta%20without%20any%20protection%20and%20only%20the%20oil%20on%20their%20body%2C%20clearly%2C%20technological%20advances%20remain%20%E2%80%9Cuntouchable%E2%80%9D%20in%20this%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20director%20uses%20Ambedkar%E2%80%99s%20original%20voice%20and%20his%20opinion%20on%20endogamy%20as%20a%20preserver%20of%20caste%20very%20succinctly%20to%20make%20a%20point.%20However%2C%20if%20you%20were%20expecting%20Ambedkar%E2%80%99s%20character%20as%20one%20of%20the%20main%20ones%2C%20you%20are%20in%20for%20a%20slight%20disappointment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPathania%20looks%20perfect%20as%20Ambedkar%20perhaps%20more%20compelling%20than%20Jabbar%20Patel%E2%80%99s%20movie%20(2000)%20where%20Mammooty%20portrayed%20the%C2%A0%20same%20character.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20is%20shown%20in%20various%20avatars%20%E2%80%94%20as%20a%20student%20of%20Columbia%20university%20on%20the%20campus%2C%20in%20and%20around%20New%20York%20and%20also%20during%20the%20Mahad%20satyagraha%20%E2%80%94%20but%20his%20screen%20presence%20is%20limited%20and%20he%20has%20no%20dialogues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20director%20had%20shown%20a%20short%20scene%20of%20Ambedkar%20presenting%20his%20paper%20%E2%80%9CCastes%20In%20India%20%E2%80%93%20Their%20Mechanism%2C%20Genesis%20and%20Development%20(1919)%E2%80%9D%20talking%20about%20endogamy%2C%20in%20front%20of%20his%20professors%2C%20his%20character%20would%20have%20come%20really%20alive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20silver%20lining%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmbedkar%E2%80%99s%20foray%20on%20the%20big%20screen%20in%20Hollywood%20in%202024%20is%20sure%20to%20enthuse%20people%20across%20the%20world%20who%20believe%20in%20human%20rights.%20It%E2%80%99s%20interesting%20to%20note%20that%20Richard%20Attenborough%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EGandhi%20%3C%2Fem%3E(1982)%20did%20not%20even%20mention%20Ambedkar%20in%20a%20passing%20reference.%20It%20seemed%20that%20he%20was%20%E2%80%98outcasted%E2%80%99%20from%20the%20scene.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%2041%20years%20later%2C%20we%20finally%20have%20a%20Hollywood%20movie%20showing%20Ambedkar%20in%20a%20motion%20picture%20led%20by%20an%20African%20American%20lead%2C%20a%20powerful%20combination%20of%20the%20oppressed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20US%2C%20the%20movie%20has%20received%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscreenrant.com%2Forigin-movie-rotten-tomatoes-ava-duvernay-movie-comparison%2F%5C%22%3Erave%3C%2Fa%3E%20reviews%20on%20%3Cem%3ERotten%20Tomatoes%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20has%20been%20appreciated%20for%20the%20incredible%20performance%20of%20the%20lead%20actor%20and%20unique%20storytelling%20by%20the%20director.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EOrigin%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20released%20in%20the%20US%20and%20the%20UK.%20The%20India%20release%20dates%20are%20not%20yet%20announced.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708335421000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2