0a%20notice%20to%20the%20Karnataka%20government%20and%20the%20complainant%20in%20the%20case%2C%20signaling%20a%20careful%20examination%20of%20the%20legal%20aspects%20surrounding%20the%20protest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Prashant%20Kumar%20went%20on%20to%20draw%20an%20intriguing%20parallel%20by%20asking%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20if%20an%20ordinary%20citizen%20had%20carried%20out%20a%20similar%20protest%3F%20Would%20the%20criminal%20case%20be%20dismissed%20in%20that%20scenario%20as%20well%3F%26quot%3B%20Justice%20Kumar%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20court%20was%20also%20referencing%20decisions%20where%20politicians%20were%20involved%2C%20raising%20concerns%20about%20the%20impartiality%20of%20the%20legal%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20in%20question%20dates%20back%20to%202022%20when%20Chief%20Minister%20Siddaramaiah%20and%20other%20Congress%20leaders%20organized%20a%20march%20to%20protest%20against%20the%20then%20Rural%20Development%20Minister%2C%20K%20S%20Eshwarappa.%20The%20protesters%20sought%20Eshwarappa's%20resignation%20following%20allegations%20of%20corruption%20related%20to%20a%20public%20work%20contract%20that%20resulted%20in%20a%20contractor%2C%20Santosh%20Patil%2C%20tragically%20taking%20his%20own%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court's%20decision%20to%20stay%20the%20proceedings%20against%20the%20Chief%20Minister%20and%20other%20leaders%20came%20as%20a%20relief%20to%20them%2C%20especially%20after%20the%20Karnataka%20High%20Court%20had%20imposed%20a%20fine%20of%20Rs%2010%2C000%20on%20each%20of%20them.%20Additionally%2C%20the%20high%20court%20had%20directed%20them%20to%20appear%20before%20a%20special%20court%20on%20March%206%2C%20which%20has%20now%20been%20put%20on%20hold%20by%20the%20top%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708330500000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2022-10%2Ftthv9vd8_supreme-court-india-generic-pti_625x300_10_October_22.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fwhat-if-common-man-does-this-supreme-court-questions-political-protests-5085904%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20raised%20questions%20on%20the%20legality%20of%20protests%20led%20by%20politicians%2C%20particularly%20highlighting%20the%20recent%20case%20involving%20Karnataka%20Chief%20Minister%20Siddaramaiah%20and%20other%20Congress%20leaders%20in%20New%20Delhi.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fwhat-if-common-man-does-this-supreme-court-questions-political-protests-5085904%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fwhat-if-common-man-does-this-supreme-court-questions-political-protests-5085904%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fwhat-if-common-man-does-this-supreme-court-questions-political-protests-5085904%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20Electoral%20Bonds%20Ban%20Will%20Do%20Little%20When%20Cash%20Is%20King%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2019-04%2Fkf7kpd38_electoral-bond-know-interesting-facts_625x300_12_April_19.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Ffinancial-support-to-political-parties-can-lead-to-quid-pro-quo-supreme-court-5061117%5C%22%3ESupreme%20Court's%3C%2Fa%3E%20decision%20last%20week%20declaring%20that%20the%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Felectoral-bonds-verdict-supreme-court-on-electoral-bonds-verdict-weighing-options-no-ordinance-yet-sources-5070428%5C%22%3E%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20unconstitutional%20as%20it%20violates%20citizens'%20right%20to%20information%20and%20may%20lead%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fvideo%2Fnews%2Fthe-big-fight%2Fwill-ban-on-electoral-bonds-clean-up-indian-politics-762177%5C%22%3Equid%20pro%20quo%20arrangements%3C%2Fa%3E%20between%20political%20parties%20and%20donors%20has%20come%20as%20a%20cause%20for%20cheer%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtvprofit.com%2Flaw-and-policy%2Fgauging-the-impact-of-supreme-courts-electoral-bonds-ruling%5C%22%3EIndia's%20opposition%20parties%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They%20believe%20they%20have%20the%20ammunition%20now%20to%20target%20the%20ruling%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20on%20corruption%20and%20puncture%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi's%20%26quot%3B%3Cem%3Ena%20khaunga%20na%20khaane%20dunga%3C%2Fem%3E%26quot%3B%20poll%20plank.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Felectoral-bonds-supreme-court-electoral-bonds-verdict-today-the-scheme-the-questions-and-the-defence-5060924%5C%22%3EThe%20opposition%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20also%20hoping%20that%20the%20top%20court's%20order%20to%20the%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20(SBI)%2C%20the%20authorised%20institution%20under%20the%20scheme%2C%20to%20reveal%20donors'%20identities%20will%20strengthen%20its%20charge%20against%20the%20BJP%20of%20indulging%20in%20crony%20capitalism%20and%20striking%20several%20quid%20pro%20quo%20deals%20with%20corporates.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202014%2C%20the%20BJP%2C%20playing%20up%20corruption%20as%20a%20major%20issue%2C%20had%20banked%20on%20the%202G%20and%20CWG%20scams%20and%20the%20controversial%20land%20deals%20made%20by%20Sonia%20Gandhi's%20son-in-law%20Robert%20Vadra%20to%20attack%20the%20Congress-led%20UPA.%20This%20time%20around%2C%20the%20BJP%20hopes%20the%20action%20of%20the%20Enforcement%20Directorate%20(ED)%20in%20several%20cases%20involving%20opposition%20players%20will%20provide%20steam%20to%20its%20'zero%20tolerance%20for%20corruption'%20plank%20and%20thus%20improve%20its%20poll%20prospects.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20opposition's%20charge%2C%20%C2%A0meanwhile%2C%20is%20that%20the%20BJP%20got%20an%20undue%20advantage%20during%20elections%20as%20it%20pocketed%20a%20majority%20of%20the%20funding%20through%20corporates.%20However%2C%20data%20shows%20this%20is%20not%20correct.%20According%20to%20the%20figures%20compiled%20by%20the%20Association%20for%20Democratic%20Reforms%20%C2%A0(ADR)%20for%2026%20tranches%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fwhat-is-an-electoral-bond-5062184%5C%22%3Eelectoral%20bonds%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20March%202018%20to%20April%202023%2C%20the%20BJP%20got%20half%20of%20a%20total%20of%20Rs.%2012%2C979%20crore%20donations%2C%20while%20the%20Congress%20and%20other%20regional%20parties%20netted%20the%20other%20half.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EAll%20Parties%20Raked%20In%20Moolah%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ADR%20data%20show%20that%20the%20BJP%2C%20the%20Congress%2C%20the%20Trinamool%20Congress%20(TMC)%2C%20the%20Biju%20Janata%20Dal%20(BJD)%20and%20the%20Dravida%20Munnetra%20Kazhagam%20(DMK)%20are%20the%20top%20five%20parties%20that%20received%20funds%20through%20electoral%20bonds%20till%20April%202022.%20While%20three%20of%20these%20are%20part%20of%20the%20opposition%20I.N.D.I.A%20bloc%2C%20the%20BJD%20is%20a%20non-aligned%20player%2C%20part%20of%20neither%20the%20BJP-led%20National%20Democratic%20Alliance%20(NDA)%20nor%20the%20INDIA%20blocs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat's%20worth%20noting%20is%20that%20though%20the%20opposition%20has%20over%20the%20years%20vociferously%20criticised%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%2C%20audit%20reports%20released%20by%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20(ECI)%20show%20that%20parties%20like%20the%20TMC%2C%20the%20Aam%20Aadmi%20Party%20(AAP)%2C%20the%20Bharat%20Rashtra%20Samithi%20(BRS)%20and%20the%20DMK%20profited%20from%20electoral%20bonds%20in%20FY2023.%20Here%20are%20a%20few%20figures%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20TMC%20got%2099.4%25%20of%20its%20total%20donations%20worth%20Rs%20327%20crore%20from%20electoral%20bonds%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EOver%2099%25%20of%20the%20DMK's%20Rs%20186%20crore%20worth%20of%20donations%20were%20in%20the%20form%20of%20electoral%20bonds%20too%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIn%202022-23%2C%20the%20AAP%20received%20Rs%2084%20crore%20worth%20of%20donations%2C%20of%20which%20over%20half%20(Rs%2045%20crore)%2C%20came%20through%20electoral%20bonds%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EOdisha%20Chief%20Minister%20Naveen%20Patnaik's%20BJD%20received%20100%25%20of%20its%20donations%20worth%20Rs%20152%20crore%20via%20electoral%20bonds%20in%20the%20last%20financial%20year%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3ESome%20Cold%20Calculations%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20of%20January%202024%2C%20the%20sum%20total%20of%20donations%20received%20by%20parties%20since%20the%20inception%20of%20the%20scheme%20in%20March%202018%20stood%20at%20Rs.%2016%2C518%20crore.%20In%20a%20way%2C%20that%20covered%20one%20period%20of%20one%20election%20cycle%20in%20the%20country%2C%20one%20Lok%20Sabha%20election%20in%202019%20and%20some%2030-odd%20Vidhan%20Sabha%20elections.%20That's%20a%20small%20share%2C%20given%20that%20the%20total%20expenditure%20in%20one%20Lok%20Sabha%20Election%20(2019)%20was%20estimated%20to%20be%20a%20whopping%20Rs.%2055%2C000-60%2C000%20crore%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Centre%20for%20Media%20Studies.%20Considering%20India%20has%20543%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats%2C%20this%20amounts%20to%20around%20Rs.%20100%20crore%20per%20seat%20on%20an%20average.%20It's%20a%20well-accepted%20fact%20now%20that%20parties%20and%20candidates%20usually%20spend%20way%20more%20than%20the%20ECI-mandated%20ceiling%20of%20Rs.%2095%20lakh%20for%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApart%20from%20this%2C%20in%20around%2030%20Vidhan%20Sabha%20elections%20in%20a%20cycle%2C%20one%20can%20easily%20assume%20that%20there%20is%20an%20expenditure%20of%20another%20Rs.%2055%2C000-60%2C000%20crore.%20There%20are%204%2C100-odd%20Vidhan%20Sabha%20seats%20in%20India%20spread%20across%20states%2C%20with%20two%20to%20three%20serious%20candidates%20vying%20for%20each%20seat%2C%20spending%20an%20average%20of%20Rs.%205%20crore%20each.%20Thus%2C%20the%20expenditure%20for%20each%20Vidhan%20Sabha%20seat%20can%20be%20taken%20to%20be%20roughly%20Rs.%2015%20cr%2C%20which%20translates%20to%20a%20total%20expenditure%20of%20around%20Rs.%2060%2C000%20cr%20across%20Vidhan%20Sabha%20polls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20compare%20this%20to%20the%20amount%20parties%20have%20disclosed%20as%20their%20expenditure%20in%20the%202019%20elections.%20According%20to%20the%20ECI%20website%2C%20some%2032%20national%20and%20regional%20parties%20together%20spent%20Rs%202%2C591%20crore%20during%20the%202019%20general%20elections%2C%20of%20which%20Rs%202%2C004%20crore-around%2077.4%25-was%20spent%20by%20seven%20national%20parties.%20This%20is%20not%20even%205%25%20of%20the%20total%20amount%20spent%20during%20elections%2C%20as%20estimated%20by%20the%20Centre%20for%20Media%20Studies.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELet's%20look%20at%20the%20amount%20spent%20by%20candidates.%20The%20ADR%20analysed%20the%20election%20expenditure%20of%20538%20MPs%20elected%20to%20Lok%20Sabha%20in%202019%2C%20and%20found%20that%20they%20spent%20Rs.%2051%20lakh%20on%20an%20average.%20However%2C%20roughly%2063%25%20of%20this%20was%20funded%20by%20their%20respective%20political%20parties.%20This%20means%20they%20spent%20on%20an%20average%20Rs.%2020%20lakh%20from%20their%20own%20pockets%20or%20other%20sources.%20The%20total%20amount%20of%20money%20spent%20by%20MPs%20then%20amounts%20to%20Rs.%20100%20crore.%20This%2C%20again%2C%20is%20a%20very%20insignificant%20amount.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3ECash%20Rules%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20all%20this%20means%20is%20that%20cash%20is%20the%20main%20source%20of%20election%20funding%20in%20India.%20Electoral%20bonds%20(Rs.%2012%2C979%20cr)%20account%20for%20just%2010%25%20of%20the%20total%20amount-around%20Rs%20120%2C000%20crore-spent%20by%20parties%20and%20candidates%20in%20one%20election%20cycle%20of%20five%20years.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20high%20possibility%20that%20with%20electoral%20bonds%20gone%20now%2C%20the%20same%20amount%20will%20take%20the%20cash%20route%20back.%20Banning%20electoral%20bonds%20doesn't%20reduce%20the%20influence%20of%20black%20money%20on%20our%20electoral%20process.%20Electoral%20bonds%20helped%20companies%20that%20do%20not%20generate%20cash%2C%20such%20as%20the%20services%20industry%2C%20to%20participate%20in%20electoral%20funding%20through%20legal%20('white')%20channels.%20That%20option%20is%20now%20closed%20for%20them.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20arguments%20being%20made%20by%20petitioners%20and%20activists%20against%20electoral%20bonds%20is%20that%20the%20ban%20would%20stop%20the%20quid%20pro%20quo%20arrangement%20between%20parties%20and%20corporations.%20However%2C%20since%20the%20actual%20amount%20received%20through%20electoral%20bonds%20is%20negligible%20and%20cash%20rules%20the%20roost%2C%20that%20quid%20pro%20quo%2C%20if%20any%2C%20isn't%20likely%20to%20be%20impacted%20by%20this%20order.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20conclusion%2C%20all%20parties%20benefited%20from%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20mechanism%2C%20the%20BJP%20the%20most%20as%20it%20is%20in%20power%20at%20the%20Centre%20and%20holds%20the%20reins%20either%20on%20its%20own%20or%20in%20alliances%20in%2018%20states.%20Parties%20like%20the%20BJD%2C%20the%20TMC%2C%20the%20DMK%20and%20the%20AAP%2C%20which%20are%20strong%20regionally%2C%20have%20also%20been%20major%20beneficiaries%2C%20but%20are%20now%20trying%20to%20milk%20the%20SC%20order%20on%20electoral%20bonds%20for%20political%20rhetoric.%20That%20may%20or%20may%20not%20work%20in%20their%20favour.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Amitabh%20Tiwari%20is%20a%20political%20strategist%20and%20commentator.%20In%20his%20earlier%20avatar%2C%20he%20was%20a%20corporate%20and%20investment%20banker.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708330380000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-10%2Fe8bgk2vo_supreme-court-getty_625x300_31_October_23.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fopinion-supreme-courts-sc-electoral-bonds-ban-will-do-little-when-cash-is-king-in-indian-politics-5086131%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Cash%20is%20the%20main%20source%20of%20election%20funding%20in%20India.%20Electoral%20bonds%20accounted%20for%20just%20around%2010%25%20of%20the%20total%20amount%20spent%20by%20parties%20and%20candidates%20in%20a%20single%20election%20cycle%20of%20five%20years%20from%202018%20to%202023.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fopinion-supreme-courts-sc-electoral-bonds-ban-will-do-little-when-cash-is-king-in-indian-politics-5086131%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fopinion-supreme-courts-sc-electoral-bonds-ban-will-do-little-when-cash-is-king-in-indian-politics-5086131%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fopinion-supreme-courts-sc-electoral-bonds-ban-will-do-little-when-cash-is-king-in-indian-politics-5086131%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Boney%20wanted%20to%20buy%20a%20home%20for%20Sridevi%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708329999000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-107816408%2Cimgsize-61132.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fboney-kapoor-expresses-a-desire-to-buy-a-home-for-his-late-wife-actress-sridevi%2Farticleshow%2F107816418.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F107816418.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EBoney%20Kapoor%20reminisces%20about%20Hyderabad%20and%20